過熱
かねつ<sup>３</sup>【過熱】 ﾛｰﾏ(kanetsu)
1 〔温度の上がりすぎ〕 overheating; getting [growing] too hot; 【物・化】 〔相変化を起こさせずに温度を上げること〕 superheating.
〜する superheat; overheat.
▲ヒーターが過熱したらすぐ切ってください.　If the heater ⌐overheats [gets too hot] turn it off immediately.
2 〔状況が異常に激しくなること〕 overheating; getting too active.
〜する overheat.
▲過熱した経済　an overheated economy; 《口》 an economy in overdrive
・経済が過熱している.　The economy ⌐has overheated [《口》 is in overdrive].
・夏になるとビール商戦が過熱する.　When summer arrives competition for beer sales ⌐heats up [《口》 goes into overdrive].
▲日本経済の過熱　overheating of the Japanese economy.
▲総選挙を前にマスコミは過熱気味だった.　With a general election approaching the media were ⌐somewhat frantic [rather over the top].
◧過熱器　a superheater.
過熱警報　a temperature alarm.
過熱蒸気　superheated ⌐steam [vapor].
過熱(蒸気)機関車　a superheated (steam) locomotive.
過熱シリンダー油　superheated steam cylinder oil.
過熱度　a [the] degree of superheat.
過熱防止器　【機・船舶】 a desuperheater.
